<p>I'm trying to enable edit mode in multiple NSTextField columns in a view-based NSTableView but I'm not sure it's doable. Here's an example of what I'm trying to achieve from an OS X app called YNAB: <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/nHmqR.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/nHmqR.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>I've tried:</p>  <pre><code>[tableView editColumn:0 row:row withEvent:nil select:NO]; [tableView editColumn:1 row:row withEvent:nil select:NO]; [tableView editColumn:2 row:row withEvent:nil select:NO]; </code></pre>  <p>And:</p>  <pre><code>[[[tableView viewAtColumn:0 row:self.selectedRow makeIfNecessary:NO] textField] becomeFirstResponder] [[[tableView viewAtColumn:1 row:self.selectedRow makeIfNecessary:NO] textField] becomeFirstResponder] [[[tableView viewAtColumn:2 row:self.selectedRow makeIfNecessary:NO] textField] becomeFirstResponder] </code></pre>  <p>But in both cases only the last NSTextField becomes in editing mode. Both <code>becomeFirstResponder</code> and <code>editColumn</code> take the focus out of current first responder and also disable editing mode. Is there a way to leave editing mode active for multiple NSTextFields?</p>  <p>Thanks</p>